### Task Management API - Example Requests

### Variables
@baseUrl = https://localhost:5001
@adminToken = {{login-admin.response.body.token}}
@userToken = {{login-user.response.body.token}}

### 1. Login as Admin
# @name login-admin
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "admin",
  "password": "admin123"
}

### 2. Login as Regular User
# @name login-user
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "user",
  "password": "user123"
}

### 3. Create Task (as User)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/tasks
Authorization: Bearer {{userToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Complete project documentation",
  "description": "Write comprehensive README and API docs",
  "dueDate": "2024-12-31T23:59:59Z"
}

### 4. Create Another Task (as User)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/tasks
Authorization: Bearer {{userToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Review code changes",
  "description": "Review pull requests",
  "dueDate": "2024-03-15T17:00:00Z"
}

### 5. Get Tasks (as User - sees only own tasks)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/tasks
Authorization: Bearer {{userToken}}

### 6. Get All Tasks (as Admin - sees all tasks)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/tasks
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### 7. Update Task (as User - own task)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/tasks/1
Authorization: Bearer {{userToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Updated: Complete project documentation",
  "description": "Write comprehensive README, API docs, and setup guide",
  "dueDate": "2024-12-31T23:59:59Z"
}

### 8. Try to Update Another User's Task (should fail with 403)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/tasks/1
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Trying to update user's task",
  "description": "This should fail",
  "dueDate": "2024-12-31T23:59:59Z"
}

### 9. Mark Task as Completed (as Admin - only admins can do this)
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/tasks/1/complete
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### 10. Try to Mark Task as Completed (as User - should fail with 403)
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/tasks/1/complete
Authorization: Bearer {{userToken}}

### 11. Create Task without Authentication (should fail with 401)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/tasks
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Unauthorized task",
  "description": "This should fail"
}

### 12. Invalid Login
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "invalid",
  "password": "wrong"
}
